[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API","page":"API","text":"","title":"API"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedAdaptiveHist","page":"API","text":"Weighted Histogram\n\nCalculate a histogram of weighted data.\n\nExample\n\n# A weighted histogram with 4 bins:\no = fit!(WeightedAdaptiveHist(4), rand(1000), rand(1000))\n\nmean(o)\nvar(o)\nstd(o)\nmedian(o)\nquantile(o, [0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.25, 1.0])\nextrema(o)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedAdaptiveHist"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedCovMatrix","page":"API","text":"WeightedCovMatrix(T = Float64)\n\nWeighted covariance matrix, tracked as a matrix of type T.\n\nAfter a call to cov the covariance matrix is stored in o.C.\n\nExample:\n\no = fit!(WeightedCovMatrix(), rand(100, 4) |> eachrow, rand(100))\no = fit!(WeightedCovMatrix(), rand(4, 100) |> eachcol, rand(100))\nsum(o)\nmean(o)\nvar(o)\nstd(o)\ncov(o)\ncor(o)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedCovMatrix"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedHist1D","page":"API","text":"WeightedHist(edges; left = true, closed = true)\n\nCreate a histogram with bin partition defined by edges.\n\nIf left, the bins will be left-closed.\nIf closed, the bin on the end will be closed.\nE.g. for a two bin histogram a b) b c) vs. a b) b c\n\nIf edges is a tuple instead of an array, a multidimensional histogram will be generated that behaves like a WeightedOnlineStat{VectorOb}.\n\nExamples\n\no = fit!(WeightedHist(-5:.1:5), randn(10^6))\n\n# approximate statistics\nusing Statistics\nmean(o)\nvar(o)\nstd(o)\nquantile(o)\nmedian(o)\nextrema(o)\narea(o)\npdf(o)\n\n2d Histogram\n\nhist2d = fit!(WeightedHist((-5:1:5, -5:1:5) ), randn(10000,2), rand(10000))\nvalue(hist2d).y\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedHist1D"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedMean","page":"API","text":"WeightedMean(T = Float64)\n\nSimple weighted mean, tracked as type T.\n\nbarx_w = fracsum_i=1^n w_ix_isum_i=1^n w_i\n\nExample:\n\no = fit!(WeightedMean(), rand(100), rand(100))\nsum(o)\nmean(o)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedMean"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedSum","page":"API","text":"WeightedSum(T = Float64)\n\nSimple weighted sum, tracked as type T.\n\nNote: This estimator has issues with catastrophic cancellation, and is not recommended for use with large numbers of samples. Use WeightedMean or WeightedVariance instead.\n\nExample:\n\no = fit!(WeightedSum(), rand(100), rand(100))\nsum(o)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedSum"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedVariance","page":"API","text":"WeightedVariance(T = Float64)\n\nSimple weighted variance, tracked as type T.\n\nThe uncorrected weighted variance is calculated as var(o, corrected = false) and is equivalent to the following formula:\n\nExample:\n\no = fit!(WeightedVariance(), rand(100), rand(100))\nsum(o)\nmean(o)\nvar(o, corrected = false)\nvar(o, corrected = true, weight_type = :frequency)\nvar(o, corrected = true, weight_type = :analytic)\nstd(o)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.WeightedVariance"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#WeightedOnlineStats.pca","page":"API","text":"`pca` creates a PCA object from a `WeightedCovMatrix` object. Requires MultivariateStats to be loaded!\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.pca"},{"category":"section","location":"#WeightedOnlineStats.jl","page":"WeightedOnlineStats.jl","text":"A version onf OnlineStats.jl allowing observations with custom weights.","title":"WeightedOnlineStats.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Basics","page":"WeightedOnlineStats.jl","text":"","title":"Basics"},{"category":"section","location":"#Creating","page":"WeightedOnlineStats.jl","text":"using WeightedOnlineStats\nm = WeightedMean()\nx = randn(100);\nw = randn(100);","title":"Creating"},{"category":"section","location":"#Updating","page":"WeightedOnlineStats.jl","text":"fit!(m, x, w)","title":"Updating"},{"category":"section","location":"#Merging","page":"WeightedOnlineStats.jl","text":"m2 = WeightedMean()\nx2 = rand(100);\nw2 = rand(100);\nfit!(m2, x2, w2)\nmerge!(m, m2)","title":"Merging"}]
